WEBVTT

00:01.543 --> 00:02.669
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: Are you ready?</i>

00:02.752 --> 00:04.170
{\an8}<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

00:04.254 --> 00:07.257
{\an8}<i>♪ I know you see me</i>
<i>standing here ♪</i>

00:08.216 --> 00:11.428
{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good,</i>
<i>my dear? ♪</i>

00:12.220 --> 00:14.597
{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good today? ♪</i>

00:14.681 --> 00:17.559
{\an8}<i>♪ Today, today ♪</i>

00:17.642 --> 00:19.728
{\an8}<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

00:20.812 --> 00:23.189
{\an8}<i>♪ I'm just another</i>
<i>kind of girl ♪</i>

00:25.233 --> 00:28.778
{\an8}<i>♪ And you want</i>
<i>to see my world ♪</i>

00:28.862 --> 00:31.698
{\an8}<i>♪ So come and run away ♪</i>

00:31.781 --> 00:33.825
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:33.908 --> 00:35.994
{\an8}<i>♪ If you wanna play ♪</i>

00:36.077 --> 00:38.037
{\an8}<i>♪ Come and play today ♪</i>

00:38.121 --> 00:42.000
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's just get away, yeah ♪</i>

00:42.083 --> 00:44.711
{\an8}<i>♪ I will make you see ♪</i>

00:44.794 --> 00:45.670
{\an8}<i>♪ All of the things ♪</i>

00:45.754 --> 00:47.797
{\an8}<i>♪ That you can be ♪</i>

00:47.881 --> 00:49.799
{\an8}<i>♪ Believe in yourself ♪</i>

00:49.883 --> 00:53.636
{\an8}<i>♪ Come follow me ♪</i>

00:53.720 --> 00:56.139
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:56.222 --> 00:57.432
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

01:00.727 --> 01:03.646
{\an8}<i>[upbeat music]</i>

01:03.730 --> 01:09.527
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:09.611 --> 01:12.405
{\an8}[indistinct chatter]

01:13.740 --> 01:16.242
{\an8}- Okay.
Fingers in.

01:19.245 --> 01:20.622
{\an8}[beeping]

01:20.705 --> 01:23.666
{\an8}- Oh, hey, Zo-eeey!
Ah!

01:23.750 --> 01:24.959
{\an8}- Interesting hello.

01:25.043 --> 01:26.961
{\an8}- We're playing
shock roulette.

01:27.045 --> 01:28.838
{\an8}- Shock roulette?
- Yeah.

01:28.922 --> 01:29.923
{\an8}You just stick
your finger in the hole,

01:30.006 --> 01:30.673
{\an8}press the button,
then someone gets

01:30.757 --> 01:32.175
{\an8}a horrible electric shock.

01:32.258 --> 01:35.553
{\an8}- Except on rare occasions
when everyone gets it.

01:35.637 --> 01:37.514
{\an8}- The quad shock.
- Wow.

01:37.597 --> 01:39.140
{\an8}I'll pass.
- Baby.

01:39.224 --> 01:42.101
{\an8}- So, guess what I'm doing
this summer.

01:42.185 --> 01:43.144
{\an8}- Uh...

01:43.228 --> 01:43.895
{\an8}- You're gonna wrestle
panda bears

01:43.978 --> 01:46.856
{\an8}on a Mississippi riverboat.

01:46.940 --> 01:48.274
{\an8}- What are you doing
this summer?

01:48.358 --> 01:50.401
{\an8}- Okay. My dad knows
this guy who manages

01:50.485 --> 01:51.653
{\an8}the Chamberlet Hotel
on Maui.

01:51.736 --> 01:53.655
{\an8}- [gasps] Isn't that where
all the celebrities stay

01:53.738 --> 01:54.489
{\an8}when they go to Hawaii?

01:54.572 --> 01:56.032
{\an8}- Yes.
And I get to work there

01:56.115 --> 01:58.034
{\an8}as a cabana girl
for the whole summer.

01:58.117 --> 01:59.702
- That's awesome!
- Yay!

01:59.786 --> 02:01.371
- And I can invite a friend.

02:01.454 --> 02:03.456
- I'm a friend.
- You wanna do it?

02:03.540 --> 02:04.874
- Yeah, but I can't.

02:04.958 --> 02:06.543
My mom's making me get
a part-time job

02:06.626 --> 02:07.669
tutoring some kids.

02:07.752 --> 02:08.586
- What kids?

02:08.669 --> 02:10.003
- I don't know.
Stupid ones?

02:10.088 --> 02:11.965
Hey.
Let's play again.

02:12.048 --> 02:12.590
Come on, Zoey.
It's fun.

02:12.674 --> 02:14.425
- Okay.

02:15.969 --> 02:18.346
- Here we go.
[beeping]

02:18.429 --> 02:20.056
- Why don't you ask
your cute boyfriend

02:20.139 --> 02:21.057
to go to Hawaii with you
for the summer?

02:21.140 --> 02:22.851
- He works for his uncle
every summer.

02:22.934 --> 02:24.185
- Hardware store.

02:24.269 --> 02:26.771
You know, hammers, paint,
copper piping.

02:26.855 --> 02:28.606
It's a thrill-a-minute.

02:28.690 --> 02:30.066
[all screaming]

02:30.149 --> 02:32.068
- This game is horrible.
- The worst.

02:32.151 --> 02:33.570
- Let's play again.
- Okay.

02:33.653 --> 02:34.571
- Yes.

02:34.654 --> 02:37.448
[beeping]

02:40.827 --> 02:42.120
- Michael,
where are you taking me?

02:42.203 --> 02:44.914
- Just keep
your eyes closed.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.666
No peeking.

02:46.749 --> 02:49.711
- Hey, Michael.
- Hey, man!

02:49.794 --> 02:50.378
- Ow!

02:50.461 --> 02:52.088
- Ooh, sorry, sorry.

02:52.755 --> 02:54.549
This way.

02:56.634 --> 02:57.969
Keep your eyes closed.

03:03.892 --> 03:07.020
Okay.
Open.

03:09.480 --> 03:12.859
- What?
Someone abandoned an old car?

03:14.027 --> 03:16.529
- Abandoned?
It's a classic.

03:16.613 --> 03:18.281
My dad gave it to me.

03:18.364 --> 03:20.700
- Oh.

03:20.783 --> 03:21.242
- Check it out.

03:22.744 --> 03:25.413
[laughs]

03:25.496 --> 03:27.123
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:27.206 --> 03:30.001
- You know how to drive
a stick shift?

03:30.084 --> 03:32.295
- Not yet.
But I'm gonna learn,

03:32.378 --> 03:34.255
and then I'm gonna drive you
to the prom in it.

03:34.339 --> 03:35.840
- But the prom
is right over there.

03:35.924 --> 03:38.426
- I will drive you.

03:38.509 --> 03:39.636
- Okay.

03:39.719 --> 03:41.596
- All right.
I gotta start practicin'.

03:43.514 --> 03:46.309
I'll begin with the super cool
"jump and sit."

03:51.064 --> 03:52.899
- Impressive.
- Yep.

03:54.817 --> 03:56.235
[engine turns over]

03:56.319 --> 03:58.029
[chuckles]

03:59.364 --> 04:02.158
[engine revving,
tires squeal]

04:05.828 --> 04:07.538
I-I got it.

04:07.622 --> 04:08.247
[engine turns over]

04:11.542 --> 04:13.294
Ha.
- Bye.

04:19.884 --> 04:22.387
[tires squeal]

04:22.470 --> 04:24.055
- [sighs]

04:24.138 --> 04:26.057
-<i> ♪ She makes me crazy ♪</i>

04:26.140 --> 04:26.724
- Quinn, Quinn, Quinn,
Quinn, Quinn!

04:26.808 --> 04:29.102
- What?

04:29.185 --> 04:30.603
- Ms. Kipper made me
head of the prom committee.

04:30.687 --> 04:32.855
I'm in charge of the whole prom.
- That's awesome.

04:32.939 --> 04:33.940
- Will you do
everything for me?

04:34.023 --> 04:36.192
- No.
- Oh, boo.

04:36.275 --> 04:37.860
- I'll work
on the prom committee.

04:37.944 --> 04:40.363
- Awesome.
Go do my laundry.

04:40.446 --> 04:42.240
- No. I meant I wanted to help
you with prom stuff.

04:42.323 --> 04:44.701
- You will be.
By doing my laundry,

04:44.784 --> 04:46.911
you're freeing up my time
to work on the prom.

04:46.995 --> 04:48.746
- Oh.
Well, that makes sense.

04:48.830 --> 04:50.206
- Good.
Run along.

04:51.541 --> 04:52.959
Okay.
Later.

04:53.042 --> 04:54.460
- Where are you goin'?
- Take a nap.

04:56.796 --> 04:57.422
- Hey.
- Ew.

05:00.008 --> 05:00.341
- Hi.

05:02.969 --> 05:04.679
I got a date to the prom.

05:04.762 --> 05:05.888
- Already?
Who?

05:05.972 --> 05:08.599
- Mandy Franklin.

05:08.683 --> 05:09.475
- Mandy F--

05:12.729 --> 05:13.730
Come on.

05:13.813 --> 05:16.065
- What?

05:16.149 --> 05:17.567
- How could you ask
Mandy Franklin to the prom?

05:17.650 --> 05:20.278
- You said we should both
ask somebody else to the prom

05:20.361 --> 05:21.946
so no one will suspect
we're dating.

05:22.030 --> 05:24.240
- Shh. Yes.

05:24.323 --> 05:26.075
But you're not taking
Make-Out Mandy.

05:26.159 --> 05:28.161
Go cancel her.
- Oh, come on.

05:28.244 --> 05:29.996
I have to get your approval
on who I ask?

05:30.079 --> 05:31.581
- Absolutely!
- Okay.

05:31.664 --> 05:33.875
Then you have to get
my approval on who you ask.

05:33.958 --> 05:35.293
- Fine.

05:35.376 --> 05:38.212
You're so irritating
sometimes.

05:38.296 --> 05:40.798
- Wanna go make-out?
- Yes.

05:40.882 --> 05:43.718
[giggles]

05:43.801 --> 05:45.720
Get your bag!
Come on!

05:45.803 --> 05:47.055
- Okay.

05:47.889 --> 05:48.931
- Okay, okay.

05:49.015 --> 05:50.558
Clutch in.

05:52.769 --> 05:54.437
First gear.

05:54.520 --> 05:54.979
Yeah!

05:55.063 --> 05:57.482
[screaming]

05:57.565 --> 05:58.566
[crash]

06:08.951 --> 06:10.536
All right, car.

06:10.620 --> 06:13.664
I'm gonna learn
to drive you, understand?

06:18.878 --> 06:21.422
- You seem frustrated.
Why?

06:22.673 --> 06:23.925
- Uh...

06:24.008 --> 06:26.302
'Cause I'm tryin'
to drive a stick shift.

06:26.385 --> 06:27.512
- Trying and failing.

06:30.014 --> 06:31.140
- Okay.
Who are you?

06:31.224 --> 06:32.975
- I'm Mr. Takato.

06:33.059 --> 06:34.644
I teach mathematics

06:34.727 --> 06:37.438
to the seventh and eighth
graders here at PCA.

06:37.522 --> 06:40.441
- Oh.
Well, that's very nice, but--

06:40.525 --> 06:44.153
- You want to drive
stick shift?

06:44.237 --> 06:47.365
- Yeah, but--
- You wish me to teach you?

06:49.617 --> 06:50.952
- Uh...

06:51.035 --> 06:52.829
Sure. Yeah.

06:52.912 --> 06:55.790
- You will do everything I say,

06:55.873 --> 06:57.667
exactly as I instruct?

06:59.335 --> 07:01.671
- Okay.
- Say yes.

07:01.754 --> 07:02.505
- Yes.

07:03.840 --> 07:08.136
- Then I will teach you
to drive stick shift.

07:08.219 --> 07:11.013
- Then I will move
the tree off my car.

07:11.097 --> 07:12.348
- Please.

07:15.852 --> 07:16.644
- All right.

07:18.312 --> 07:20.940
<i>MAN: ♪ Good-bye to love ♪</i>

07:21.023 --> 07:26.195
<i>♪ It never seems so far away ♪</i>

07:26.279 --> 07:27.613
<i>♪ Give it-- ♪</i>

07:27.697 --> 07:28.865
- Hello.

07:28.948 --> 07:30.867
- You scared me.

07:30.950 --> 07:34.370
- Good.
Now I can comfort you.

07:34.453 --> 07:35.329
Shh.
It's okay.

07:35.413 --> 07:37.290
You're safe now.
- [laughs]

07:37.373 --> 07:39.375
Where have you been
all night?

07:39.458 --> 07:41.210
I texted you,
like, five times.

07:41.294 --> 07:42.128
- I was on the phone
with my uncle.

07:42.211 --> 07:44.255
- Hardware Hank?
- Not anymore.

07:44.338 --> 07:47.091
He sold it.
- He sold his hardware store?

07:47.175 --> 07:48.926
- Yup.
And guess what that means.

07:49.010 --> 07:50.094
- No more free hammers?

07:50.178 --> 07:52.722
- I can go with you
to Hawaii this summer.

07:52.805 --> 07:53.848
- Really?
Wow.

07:53.931 --> 07:57.268
- And here's
some more good news.

07:57.351 --> 07:58.686
- What's this?

08:01.981 --> 08:03.399
Oh, my God.

08:03.482 --> 08:07.236
What'd you do?
- You like it?

08:07.320 --> 08:09.530
- I love it.
What's this for?

08:09.614 --> 08:11.908
- I don't know.
I was thinkin' maybe your neck?

08:11.991 --> 08:15.077
- Come on. Seriously.
Why'd you buy me this?

08:15.161 --> 08:17.788
- Because I--

08:19.123 --> 08:21.375
I--uh--

08:21.459 --> 08:25.004
Read what it says
on the back.

08:25.087 --> 08:26.672
<i>MAN: ♪ We can change ♪</i>

08:26.756 --> 08:29.133
<i>♪ If you just</i>
<i>want to change ♪</i>

08:29.217 --> 08:31.093
- It says, "I love you."

08:31.177 --> 08:32.803
<i>MAN: ♪ Whoa, yeah ♪</i>

08:32.886 --> 08:35.932
<i>♪ Whoa-oh-oh ♪</i>

08:36.015 --> 08:39.602
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:39.684 --> 08:43.563
♪ Oh ♪

08:46.525 --> 08:49.362
[girls screaming]

08:52.490 --> 08:53.533
- I'm thirsty.

08:54.867 --> 08:58.454
- Okay. You are being
way too casual about this.

08:58.538 --> 08:59.622
One of the hottest guys at PCA
just gave you a necklace

08:59.705 --> 09:03.334
and told you he loves you
at the same time.

09:03.417 --> 09:05.127
- They make
Apple Berry Blix now?

09:05.211 --> 09:06.087
Apples aren't berries.

09:06.170 --> 09:08.297
- Oh.
- What's with you?

09:08.381 --> 09:10.508
- Don't you love James back?

09:10.591 --> 09:12.426
- Well, yeah, I think.

09:12.510 --> 09:14.804
- Okay.
I know what's going on here.

09:14.887 --> 09:17.265
- Do you?
- You're in "I love you" shock.

09:17.348 --> 09:19.308
- Oh, God.
- Quinn?

09:19.392 --> 09:21.477
- Oh, absolutely.
It's a teen girl thing.

09:21.560 --> 09:23.980
I read about it
on highschoolcrazy.com.

09:24.063 --> 09:25.189
- Oh, yeah.
I saw that.

09:25.273 --> 09:26.565
Zoey, come look.

09:30.027 --> 09:31.487
- Okay.

09:31.570 --> 09:34.907
Highschoolcrazy.com.

09:34.991 --> 09:36.075
- I love this site.

09:36.158 --> 09:37.201
- Oh.
Okay, there.

09:37.285 --> 09:38.369
Click on "I love you shock."

09:38.452 --> 09:39.620
- I know what to do.

09:40.496 --> 09:42.999
- See, Zoey?
There it is.

09:43.082 --> 09:45.376
[door shuts]

09:58.931 --> 10:00.224
- Are you ready?

10:00.308 --> 10:02.018
- Sure.
Yeah.

10:02.101 --> 10:02.893
Let's drive.

10:04.729 --> 10:05.813
What?

10:05.896 --> 10:07.523
- You cannot learn
to drive a stick shift

10:07.606 --> 10:11.485
until you learn to drive
a stick shift.

10:13.487 --> 10:13.779
- What does--

10:17.033 --> 10:19.493
I don't even know
what you just said.

10:19.577 --> 10:23.831
I mean, stick shift--

10:23.914 --> 10:24.582
What's that?

10:24.665 --> 10:27.209
- A wooden bowl containing

10:27.293 --> 10:31.505
tuna, mayonnaise, and onions.

10:32.923 --> 10:33.674
- And?

10:35.092 --> 10:36.677
- Mix it.
- Mix it?

10:36.761 --> 10:39.722
- I want you to make
tuna salad.

10:39.805 --> 10:41.766
- But why?
- Mix the tuna.

10:51.901 --> 10:53.402
Your right hand.

10:55.071 --> 10:55.696
- Okay.
Right hand.

10:57.990 --> 10:59.033
- No.

11:00.159 --> 11:02.995
Up, down,

11:03.079 --> 11:06.207
over,
up, down.

11:06.290 --> 11:09.168
- Up, down, up--

11:09.251 --> 11:10.252
- Over.

11:10.336 --> 11:12.671
- Over, up, down.

11:12.755 --> 11:13.714
- Again.

11:13.798 --> 11:17.510
- Up, down, over, up, down.

11:17.593 --> 11:19.470
Up, down, over, up, down.

11:19.553 --> 11:21.597
- Stir the tuna.

11:21.680 --> 11:22.431
- Up, down, over, up, down.

11:22.515 --> 11:26.268
- Stir the tuna
with your soul.

11:26.352 --> 11:28.187
- With my soul.

11:28.270 --> 11:31.941
Up, down, over,
up, down.

11:32.024 --> 11:33.150
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

11:33.234 --> 11:36.612
[horn honks]

11:40.866 --> 11:44.120
- Okay.
What about that girl there?

11:44.203 --> 11:45.538
- Absolutely not.

11:45.621 --> 11:47.832
No way are you taking her
to the prom.

11:47.915 --> 11:50.459
- Why?
- She's way too pretty.

11:50.543 --> 11:54.046
- Oh, don't be a baby.
- All right.

11:54.130 --> 11:56.298
If you get to go with her,

11:56.382 --> 11:59.885
I get to go with...him.

12:02.138 --> 12:05.141
- You're not going to the dance
with Shirtless Dave.

12:05.224 --> 12:06.267
- Okay.

12:06.350 --> 12:10.146
Then what about, uh...

12:10.771 --> 12:11.313
- Hi.
- Whoa.

12:11.397 --> 12:13.566
- Hi.
- Hello.

12:13.649 --> 12:15.734
- Have you guys
seen Zoey today?

12:15.818 --> 12:17.820
- Yeah. Why?
- Sure.

12:17.903 --> 12:18.946
- 'Cause we usually meet
at the coffee cart

12:19.029 --> 12:21.449
in the morning,
and she wasn't there,

12:21.532 --> 12:24.493
and she hasn't checked her
voicemail or texted me all day.

12:24.577 --> 12:25.995
- Well, bye.

12:27.079 --> 12:29.331
- I can always
count on you for help.

12:29.415 --> 12:31.625
- [chuckles]
- Yeah.

12:34.837 --> 12:37.089
- Now will you just let me pick
a date for the prom already?

12:37.173 --> 12:39.175
- No.
- But you said--

12:39.258 --> 12:41.969
- We'll never agree
if we pick our own dates.

12:42.052 --> 12:44.013
So why don't we pick
each others?

12:44.096 --> 12:47.850
- What, you mean, you pick
my date and I pick yours?

12:47.933 --> 12:50.686
- Yeah, that way you'll
be okay with whoever I take

12:50.769 --> 12:53.731
and I'll be okay
with whoever you take.

12:53.814 --> 12:54.982
- Okay.
I guess that's fair.

12:57.276 --> 12:59.945
Can I at least give you an idea
of who I'd like to take?

13:00.029 --> 13:00.779
- Sure.

13:01.947 --> 13:03.699
- See those twins
over there?

13:03.782 --> 13:07.411
- Yes.
Which one do you want?

13:07.495 --> 13:07.912
- Both.

13:10.956 --> 13:12.041
Ow!

13:12.124 --> 13:14.001
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:14.084 --> 13:17.046
<i>[Eastern music]</i>

13:17.129 --> 13:22.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:22.468 --> 13:25.012
- This feels nasty.

13:25.095 --> 13:27.556
And I don't get this.
I don't get this at all.

13:27.640 --> 13:30.559
- Keep stomping the grapes.

13:30.643 --> 13:31.936
- But I want to learn
to drive a stick shift.

13:33.854 --> 13:36.565
- This tuna fish
is excellent.

13:36.649 --> 13:38.234
- Thanks.

13:40.361 --> 13:43.239
- Slow down!

13:43.322 --> 13:47.243
Move your feet rhythmically.

13:47.326 --> 13:49.411
Left, right,

13:49.495 --> 13:51.580
left, right,

13:51.664 --> 13:54.750
left,
right.

13:54.833 --> 13:57.628
- Yeah, yeah.
Left, right, left, right.

14:01.215 --> 14:03.425
You said you were gonna teach me
to drive a stick shift.

14:03.509 --> 14:05.636
And now I've spend almost
two days doing nothing

14:05.719 --> 14:06.762
but making you tuna fish salad
in a square bowl

14:06.845 --> 14:09.265
and grape juice
with my bare feet.

14:09.348 --> 14:09.890
- Silence!

14:15.771 --> 14:17.606
You are ready.

14:17.690 --> 14:24.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:24.405 --> 14:25.739
- Now what?

14:25.823 --> 14:29.159
- Put your key in the slot

14:29.243 --> 14:30.786
then twist it.

14:33.872 --> 14:34.999
[engine turns over]

14:37.209 --> 14:38.877
Now drive this car.

14:40.296 --> 14:42.464
- I don't know how to drive
a stick shift.

14:42.548 --> 14:44.592
- Stomp the grapes.

14:45.843 --> 14:47.094
- But--
- Stir the tuna!

14:50.222 --> 14:51.890
Stomp the grapes.

14:54.101 --> 14:56.061
Stir the tuna.

14:58.897 --> 15:02.776
<i>MAN: ♪ Whatever turns you on ♪</i>

15:03.569 --> 15:06.113
- Stomp the grapes.

15:08.157 --> 15:09.325
Stir the tuna!

15:11.160 --> 15:11.952
- [chuckles]

15:12.786 --> 15:15.372
Hey, I'm drivin'.

15:15.456 --> 15:16.665
- Indeed.

15:16.749 --> 15:19.501
Stomp the grapes.

15:19.585 --> 15:21.837
Stir the tuna.

15:21.920 --> 15:23.964
- Hey, this is fun!

15:24.048 --> 15:26.008
- Grapes.
- Grapes.

15:26.091 --> 15:28.510
- Tuna fish.
- Tuna fish.

15:28.594 --> 15:30.846
[laughter]

15:30.929 --> 15:35.726
<i>MAN: ♪ Whatever turns you on ♪</i>

15:35.809 --> 15:39.772
<i>♪ Whatever, whatever ♪</i>

15:39.855 --> 15:40.939
<i>♪ Whatever turns you on ♪</i>

15:41.023 --> 15:44.401
- I'm drivin'!
Whoo-hoo!

15:44.485 --> 15:46.028
[honks horn]

15:46.111 --> 15:48.155
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:48.238 --> 15:50.282
- Okay. I put Stacey in charge
of prom decorations,

15:50.366 --> 15:52.618
food, snacks, and beverages
and booking the band.

15:52.701 --> 15:55.746
- And what are you doing?

15:55.829 --> 15:57.039
- I'm telling Stacey
what to do.

15:57.122 --> 15:58.749
Now, you can
either be in charge

15:58.832 --> 15:59.958
of getting
the photographer or ice.

16:00.042 --> 16:03.337
- Ice?
- You know, frozen water.

16:03.420 --> 16:05.547
Keeps drinks cold.
Often comes in cube form.

16:05.631 --> 16:07.841
- Yeah. Thanks.

16:07.925 --> 16:09.301
But, I don't wanna help
with the prom.

16:09.385 --> 16:12.304
- Why not?
- I'm just not that in to it.

16:12.388 --> 16:15.057
- But this is your first
big dance with James.

16:15.140 --> 16:16.350
- So?

16:16.433 --> 16:18.018
- So you were all excited
about it two weeks ago.

16:18.102 --> 16:20.729
- And now, I'm--
- [clears throat]

16:20.813 --> 16:22.398
- Hey, Zoey.

16:22.481 --> 16:24.733
- Hi.
- Hey, James.

16:24.817 --> 16:26.568
- Where have you been
the past two days?

16:26.652 --> 16:28.737
- I've been around.

16:28.821 --> 16:30.155
- Uh, not around me.

16:31.865 --> 16:34.243
- I'll see you, guys, later.

16:37.621 --> 16:39.790
- Nice necklace.
- This?

16:39.873 --> 16:41.750
I've had it like forever.

16:41.834 --> 16:43.419
- I know.

16:43.502 --> 16:45.921
So why do I feel like
you don't want me around?

16:46.004 --> 16:47.798
- Come on,
you're my boyfriend.

16:47.881 --> 16:49.508
Why would I won't you around?

16:49.591 --> 16:52.428
- Good question.

16:52.511 --> 16:54.930
So you wanna get some dinner
at Sushi Rox?

16:55.013 --> 16:57.641
I'll play you a cool drum solo
with my chopsticks.

16:57.725 --> 16:59.601
- Yeah.
I got a ton of homework

16:59.685 --> 17:01.937
and the whole ice thing
for the prom.

17:02.020 --> 17:05.107
- So you will to the ice?
- Yes.

17:05.190 --> 17:06.483
- Yay.

17:06.567 --> 17:08.944
- Right.
So maybe tomorrow night?

17:09.028 --> 17:10.445
- I'll call you later.

17:12.364 --> 17:15.284
<i>[gentle music]</i>

17:15.367 --> 17:19.829
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:19.913 --> 17:23.040
- No.
- You have to.

17:23.125 --> 17:24.084
- Quinn.

17:24.167 --> 17:25.919
- Our deal was
I get to pick your date

17:26.002 --> 17:27.463
to the prom
and you get to pick mine.

17:27.546 --> 17:28.088
Now go ask her.

17:42.770 --> 17:44.396
- Hey, Stacey.

17:44.480 --> 17:46.023
- Oh, Logan.
Hi. Eeh.

17:46.106 --> 17:50.569
- Uh, you got
a date to the prom?

17:50.652 --> 17:52.237
- Well, no.

17:52.321 --> 17:55.783
But look, I'm building
one enormous cotton swab

17:55.866 --> 17:59.703
outta lots of regular
cotton swabs.

17:59.787 --> 18:01.038
- Yeah.

18:03.123 --> 18:06.418
So do you wanna go
to the prom with me?

18:07.086 --> 18:09.046
Feel free to say no.

18:09.129 --> 18:11.840
- Yes. Yes.
Yes!

18:11.924 --> 18:15.511
My first prom,
and with Logan Reese.

18:15.594 --> 18:17.137
I gotta go shave my toes.

18:18.138 --> 18:20.724
Only my big ones grow hair.

18:20.808 --> 18:23.519
Ah!
Mrs. Stacey Reese.

18:24.645 --> 18:26.897
- [sighs]

18:30.818 --> 18:33.529
- It won't be that bad.

18:33.612 --> 18:36.532
- Yeah, sure.

18:36.615 --> 18:40.786
Now...

18:40.869 --> 18:43.121
let's talk
about your prom date.

18:44.373 --> 18:47.835
- Would you like to go
to the prom with me?

18:51.463 --> 18:54.174
- Okay. But only 'cause
you're my sister's friend.

18:58.887 --> 18:59.179
- Thanks.

19:01.682 --> 19:04.601
<i>[somber music]</i>

19:04.685 --> 19:08.438
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:08.522 --> 19:12.484
<i>WOMAN: ♪ Every now and then</i>
<i>I write but never send ♪</i>

19:12.568 --> 19:15.571
<i>♪ A letter off to you ♪</i>

19:15.654 --> 19:17.406
<i>♪ Sometimes when I sleep ♪</i>

19:17.489 --> 19:21.201
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:21.285 --> 19:24.788
- You know,
they're not gonna pop.

19:24.872 --> 19:26.290
- Hey.

19:31.003 --> 19:31.920
- Finish your homework?

19:32.004 --> 19:35.007
- Homework?
- Yeah.

19:35.090 --> 19:36.925
Earlier you said you'd--
- Oh, yeah.

19:37.009 --> 19:38.594
I finished it a while ago.

19:38.677 --> 19:39.678
- Cool.

19:39.761 --> 19:43.432
So...wanna break up?

19:43.515 --> 19:45.225
- What?

19:45.309 --> 19:47.060
- It wasn't that easy
to say the first time.

19:47.144 --> 19:49.062
Do I have to say it again?

19:49.146 --> 19:51.523
- Why do you wanna
break up with me?

19:51.607 --> 19:52.941
- I didn't say I did.

19:53.025 --> 19:54.568
I asked you if you did.

19:56.278 --> 19:57.738
- Okay, what's going on?

19:57.821 --> 20:00.282
- You tell me.

20:00.365 --> 20:03.493
Come on, Saturday night
I gave you a necklace

20:03.577 --> 20:05.120
that said I love you.

20:05.203 --> 20:07.414
Since then
you've barely talked to me.

20:07.497 --> 20:10.459
And when you did,
you didn't exactly say it back.

20:14.046 --> 20:15.839
- I'm sorry.

20:15.923 --> 20:17.382
- It's okay.

20:17.466 --> 20:18.800
- I don't want you to hate me.

20:18.884 --> 20:20.260
- I don't hate you.

20:20.344 --> 20:23.263
Didn't you read
the necklace?

20:24.514 --> 20:25.891
I meant it.

20:25.974 --> 20:27.768
I do love you,

20:27.851 --> 20:30.604
whether you're my girlfriend
or just my friend.

20:32.147 --> 20:34.650
- Okay.
Now you're making me hate you.

20:34.733 --> 20:38.195
- How am I--
- 'Cause you're awesome.

20:38.278 --> 20:40.405
You're like the nicest,
coolest guy I've ever met.

20:43.450 --> 20:46.328
Look, James, when
you gave me that necklace--

20:46.411 --> 20:49.831
- Come on. Things were
getting weird between us

20:49.915 --> 20:52.793
before I gave you
the necklace.

20:52.876 --> 20:54.461
You wanna tell me why?

20:56.922 --> 21:00.133
- I don't know.

21:00.217 --> 21:02.511
There's just...

21:02.594 --> 21:05.013
something in the way.

21:05.764 --> 21:07.349
I can't figure it out.

21:09.101 --> 21:09.393
- I get it.

21:11.520 --> 21:15.107
Look, I'm not mad
or anything like that.

21:16.149 --> 21:17.275
I want us to be friends.

21:17.901 --> 21:19.361
- I do too.

21:20.696 --> 21:22.489
- Good.

21:24.366 --> 21:27.077
<i>WOMAN: ♪ It's just you ♪</i>

21:27.160 --> 21:30.622
<i>♪ Who tears me in two ♪</i>

21:30.706 --> 21:32.082
<i>♪ Yeah it's you ♪</i>

21:32.165 --> 21:35.711
<i>♪ Oh, it's you ♪</i>

21:35.794 --> 21:37.045
- Keep it.

21:37.129 --> 21:39.172
<i>WOMAN: ♪ It's you</i>
<i>that I'd lie for ♪</i>

21:39.256 --> 21:42.300
<i>♪ You that I'd die for ♪</i>

21:42.384 --> 21:45.178
<i>♪ But I've got to move on ♪</i>

21:45.262 --> 21:47.305
<i>♪ Without you ♪</i>

21:47.389 --> 21:50.851
<i>♪ Well, it's time</i>
<i>to move on ♪</i>

21:50.934 --> 21:53.395
<i>♪ Without you ♪</i>

21:53.478 --> 21:57.566
<i>♪ I've just got to move on ♪</i>

21:57.649 --> 22:00.027
<i>♪ Got to move on ♪</i>

22:00.110 --> 22:02.696
<i>♪ Without you ♪</i>

22:02.779 --> 22:07.743
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:09.536 --> 22:11.246
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

22:11.329 --> 22:14.041
- Okay.
What do you think?

22:14.124 --> 22:15.792
Am I prom ready?

22:15.876 --> 22:18.003
- Yeah, but don't you think that
dress is a little too sexy

22:18.086 --> 22:21.089
for your date, Dustin?

22:21.173 --> 22:23.717
- Dustin's very mature
for his age.

22:23.800 --> 22:26.511
- Yeah. I hear his bedtime
got moved up to 8:15.

22:31.391 --> 22:32.934
- Everybody dressed?
- Yeah.

22:33.018 --> 22:35.645
- Pretty much.

22:35.729 --> 22:37.439
- What's up, hot stuff?

22:37.522 --> 22:40.108
- Just getting ready,
equally hot stuff.

22:41.985 --> 22:43.278
- So before
we go to the prom,

22:43.361 --> 22:45.280
you and I are going to
Pete and Sam's for dinner.

22:45.363 --> 22:48.116
- I love Pete and Sam's.
- I know.

22:48.200 --> 22:50.619
- We're not going.
- Why?

22:50.702 --> 22:52.996
You know how hard it was
to get reservations?

22:53.080 --> 22:54.081
- We have to get to the prom.

22:54.164 --> 22:55.248
- We'll be at
the prom on time.

22:55.332 --> 22:57.209
- No.
On time is for losers.

22:57.292 --> 22:59.377
I wanna be fashionably late.

22:59.461 --> 23:01.505
- I'm taking you
to Pete and Sam's,

23:01.588 --> 23:04.257
and we'll get to the prom
perfectly late, all right?

23:04.341 --> 23:06.134
- All right.
- Be more psyched.

23:06.218 --> 23:09.096
- All right!
- Good girl.

23:11.139 --> 23:12.516
- Hey, Vince.
- Hey, Zoey.

23:12.599 --> 23:14.434
- Later, Vince.
- Later, Zoey.

23:22.109 --> 23:24.653
- A dress just landed on me.

23:26.863 --> 23:28.573
Ooh, and a strapless bra.

23:28.657 --> 23:30.951
- Put that stuff on.
- With these shoes.

23:31.034 --> 23:35.163
- Okay, for, like, the 97th
time, I'm not going to the prom.

23:35.247 --> 23:36.498
- Just 'cause
you broke up with James

23:36.581 --> 23:38.250
doesn't mean you have to be
the only person at PCA

23:38.333 --> 23:39.501
who's not gonna be there.

23:39.584 --> 23:40.335
- Lots of people
are going dateless.

23:40.418 --> 23:43.713
- Yeah.
Firewire and, uh...

23:43.797 --> 23:44.923
Firewire.

23:45.006 --> 23:47.008
- That weird Swedish kid
that smells like meat.

23:47.092 --> 23:47.968
- Yeah.

23:48.051 --> 23:49.678
- Will you guys
just go have fun?

23:49.761 --> 23:50.762
- Not without you.
- Why couldn't you

23:50.846 --> 23:53.306
have broken up with James
after the prom?

23:53.390 --> 23:54.683
- Why'd you break up
with him at all?

23:54.766 --> 23:55.976
- He's awesome.

23:56.059 --> 23:57.686
- I know James is awesome,
and I know you think

23:57.769 --> 23:58.770
I was stupid
to break up with him.

23:58.854 --> 24:00.522
And maybe you're right.
But I did it.

24:00.605 --> 24:02.524
And now, it's done.
Oh, my God.

24:02.607 --> 24:04.776
Those shoes are cute.
- Then wear them to the prom.

24:04.860 --> 24:06.153
- Not happening!

24:07.279 --> 24:10.699
- Zoey, something's
bothering you.

24:10.782 --> 24:12.534
- Yeah.

24:14.286 --> 24:16.288
If you figure out what it is,
let me know.

24:22.294 --> 24:24.504
- [sighs]
This is so bad.

24:29.467 --> 24:33.305
- Logan Reese,
prepare for the most

24:33.388 --> 24:34.639
spectacular night
of your life.

24:38.894 --> 24:40.645
Let's rock this prom!

24:40.729 --> 24:42.731
Argh!
Whoo!

24:42.814 --> 24:44.316
- [groans]

24:45.442 --> 24:48.695
- I'm here.
- Oh, hi, Dustin.

24:48.778 --> 24:51.781
- I know I'm supposed
to bring you a flower,

24:51.865 --> 24:52.532
but I forgot, so here.

24:56.578 --> 24:59.331
- Wow.
A Canadian dollar.

25:00.165 --> 25:02.292
I'll be ready in a sec.

25:12.093 --> 25:14.221
- What are these?

25:14.304 --> 25:15.680
- Give me that.

25:17.849 --> 25:20.352
These are small
spherical explosives

25:20.435 --> 25:22.145
I made out of plutronium.

25:22.229 --> 25:22.646
- What do they do?

25:31.446 --> 25:34.574
- This is so embarrassing.
- What?

25:34.658 --> 25:36.618
- Going to the prom
without dates.

25:36.701 --> 25:38.954
- I could have gotten a date
if I wanted.

25:39.037 --> 25:40.956
- Who?
[screaming]

25:41.039 --> 25:43.083
- Awesome!

25:43.166 --> 25:46.419
[all coughing]

25:46.503 --> 25:49.506
- Come on.
Let's go to the prom.

25:51.508 --> 25:53.510
- What was that?
- I don't know.

25:53.593 --> 25:54.803
- I do.

25:54.886 --> 25:58.306
Remember "Doomsday" comic book
issue number three?

25:58.390 --> 25:59.766
- The end of the world.

25:59.849 --> 26:01.601
- Qwanfar said,
"The end of the world

26:01.685 --> 26:03.144
"will be signaled
by a series of small,

26:03.228 --> 26:05.480
mysterious explosions."

26:05.563 --> 26:07.440
- Black Doomsday has begun.

26:07.524 --> 26:10.235
- According to Qwanfar,
the only survivors will be those

26:10.318 --> 26:11.778
who dwell in the wilderness.

26:11.861 --> 26:12.821
- Let's go!

26:12.904 --> 26:14.656
[all screaming]

26:17.993 --> 26:19.661
<i>MAN: The Pacific</i>
<i>Coast Academy prom</i>

26:19.744 --> 26:21.788
<i>will officially begin</i>
<i>in one hour.</i>

26:21.871 --> 26:23.123
<i>Please sign in</i>
<i>at the registration desk</i>

26:23.206 --> 26:25.041
<i>with Mr. Bender.</i>

26:25.125 --> 26:26.793
[horn honks]

26:26.876 --> 26:34.634
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:41.850 --> 26:42.183
- My lady.

26:42.267 --> 26:45.478
[laughs]

26:45.562 --> 26:46.688
You didn't think
I could do it, did you?

26:46.771 --> 26:48.773
- No, I did not think
you can learn

26:48.857 --> 26:50.525
how to drive a stick shift
that well, that fast.

26:50.608 --> 26:53.236
- I owe it all to Mr. Takato.

26:53.320 --> 26:55.488
Stirrin' tuna fish,
stomping grapes.

26:55.572 --> 26:56.906
The man's
a stick shiftin' genius.

26:56.990 --> 26:59.034
- How come I've never heard
of this teacher before?

26:59.117 --> 27:02.162
- I told you.
He's a lower school teacher.

27:02.245 --> 27:03.747
- Okay.

27:09.544 --> 27:11.629
- This is so uncomfortable.

27:11.713 --> 27:14.716
- Would you quit complainin'?

27:21.014 --> 27:23.350
Ha! You fell off.

27:23.433 --> 27:25.560
- Yes.
Wasn't that hilarious?

27:27.228 --> 27:30.065
- [laughs]

27:30.148 --> 27:33.234
Your date brought you
to the prom on a bicycle?

27:33.318 --> 27:35.904
[laughs]
That's hilarious.

27:35.987 --> 27:37.238
- Hey, Dustin, is there
a lower school teacher

27:37.322 --> 27:39.240
named Mr. Takato?

27:39.324 --> 27:40.909
- I never heard of him.

27:40.992 --> 27:43.828
But, hey, did you see Quinn
fall off my bike?

27:43.912 --> 27:46.581
[laughter]

27:52.337 --> 27:55.465
- Let's go dance.

27:56.299 --> 28:04.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:04.682 --> 28:06.267
[indistinct chatter]

28:06.351 --> 28:08.353
- Lisa, Michael, Quinn!

28:08.436 --> 28:10.230
- Hey, guys.
- Stacey!

28:10.313 --> 28:12.190
Nice to see you

28:12.273 --> 28:14.484
with your date.

28:15.485 --> 28:16.820
- Yeah, that's right.

28:25.120 --> 28:27.622
- I can't believe you made me
come here with Dustin.

28:27.705 --> 28:29.749
- Oh. And I'm having
a blast with Stacey.

28:31.209 --> 28:33.336
- Maybe we should have just
come here together.

28:33.420 --> 28:34.921
- And let everyone know
we like each other?

28:35.004 --> 28:36.589
- No. I couldn't take
the abuse we'd get.

28:36.673 --> 28:39.551
- Me neither.
- Logie, come on.

28:39.634 --> 28:41.845
- I'm coming!
- [grunts]

28:42.887 --> 28:45.932
- Look, I promise,
sometime tonight,

28:46.015 --> 28:50.520
we'll find a way to sneak off
and be together.

28:50.603 --> 28:52.397
- I like you.

28:52.480 --> 28:55.108
- Logan, what's the holdup,
buttercup?

28:56.985 --> 29:00.196
- I was just telling Quinn
how much I don't like her.

29:00.280 --> 29:00.738
- Yes, you're such a jerk.

29:02.532 --> 29:03.908
- Let's go, Dillsen.

29:06.077 --> 29:07.787
- Sure thing, Reese.

29:09.914 --> 29:11.833
- [sighs]

29:16.421 --> 29:17.839
- What happened back there?

29:17.922 --> 29:19.883
I woke up on the ground
and some janitor

29:19.966 --> 29:21.843
was trying
to steal my wallet.

29:21.926 --> 29:23.470
- Wah.

29:23.553 --> 29:29.058
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:29.142 --> 29:30.643
<i>MAN: ♪ I'm lookin'</i>
<i>for answers ♪</i>

29:30.727 --> 29:35.231
<i>♪ But I'm already late ♪</i>

29:35.315 --> 29:36.191
<i>♪ You say you need me ♪</i>

29:36.274 --> 29:39.944
<i>♪ One more... ♪</i>

29:40.028 --> 29:41.404
- Oh. Hey, Zoey.

29:41.488 --> 29:44.699
- Hi.
- One sec.

29:45.742 --> 29:48.328
Aren't you going to the prom?

29:48.411 --> 29:49.704
- No. I don't have a date.

29:49.787 --> 29:51.498
- I'll be your date.

29:52.415 --> 29:53.833
- You're taking Martha.

29:57.754 --> 29:59.380
- I'll get rid of her.

29:59.464 --> 30:02.050
- Jeremiah.
- Yes?

30:02.133 --> 30:02.884
- Go.

30:04.594 --> 30:06.012
- All right.

30:06.095 --> 30:09.432
<i>MAN:</i>
<i>♪ Like you're so unaware ♪</i>

30:09.516 --> 30:10.683
<i>♪ You're looking for answers ♪</i>

30:10.767 --> 30:14.771
<i>♪ But you're already there ♪</i>

30:14.854 --> 30:19.442
<i>♪ I turn around</i>
<i>and I see little baby ♪</i>

30:19.526 --> 30:21.361
<i>♪ That you've gone away ♪</i>

30:21.444 --> 30:27.075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:31.621 --> 30:33.915
- Gidget. Gidget. Gidget!

30:33.998 --> 30:36.960
Look, what do you
want from me?

30:37.043 --> 30:39.170
[sniffs]

30:39.254 --> 30:41.923
Well, then why didn't you say
that before we got married?

30:43.841 --> 30:44.926
- Hey, what time is it?

30:45.009 --> 30:46.594
DRIVER: Oh, oh, oh, okay.
No.

30:46.678 --> 30:48.680
- Quarter to eight.
- Perfect.

30:48.763 --> 30:51.307
DRIVER: Your mother's an animal!

30:51.391 --> 30:53.101
Animal!

30:53.184 --> 30:55.061
Yeah, okay, well,
if your ex-boyfriend

30:55.144 --> 30:58.106
is so rich and successful,
then maybe you should

30:58.189 --> 30:59.857
have married him.

30:59.941 --> 31:01.401
Gidget.

31:01.484 --> 31:02.610
Gidget! Gidget!
- Yikes.

31:02.694 --> 31:04.779
- You don't want me
to be a cab driver?

31:04.862 --> 31:06.906
You want me to go
to community college?

31:06.990 --> 31:08.408
Fine.
I'll go right now.

31:08.491 --> 31:10.952
[tires squeal]

31:16.874 --> 31:19.794
You hear that?
I'm not a cab driver anymore.

31:19.877 --> 31:22.046
No, no, no--
Here go the keys.

31:23.464 --> 31:26.092
You happy?

31:27.552 --> 31:29.095
Animal!

31:29.554 --> 31:31.264
- Ahh!

31:32.432 --> 31:34.434
DRIVER: [yelling]

31:34.517 --> 31:36.603
- He's leaving.

31:36.686 --> 31:37.770
- Yeah, I see that.

31:37.854 --> 31:39.564
- But we have to get
to the prom.

31:39.647 --> 31:41.608
- Yeah, I understand
the conflict here.

31:41.691 --> 31:44.485
Hey, buddy! Would you
please come back here?

31:44.569 --> 31:45.903
- No!

31:45.987 --> 31:48.781
I gotta go register
for classes!

31:58.166 --> 32:01.127
<i>[rock music]</i>

32:01.210 --> 32:07.216
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:07.300 --> 32:09.427
- All right, fellow PCA
students and faculty.

32:09.510 --> 32:13.431
My friend Lola was supposed
to kick off this prom tonight,

32:13.514 --> 32:14.390
but she's a little late.

32:14.474 --> 32:17.310
So here I go.
Who's ready?

32:17.393 --> 32:20.188
[all cheering]

32:21.648 --> 32:24.317
Then let's prom it up!

32:24.400 --> 32:28.196
[cheers and applause]

32:28.279 --> 32:29.864
<i>[rock music]</i>

32:29.947 --> 32:32.075
<i>- ♪ A little good advice ♪</i>

32:32.158 --> 32:35.870
<i>♪ To get you</i>
<i>through the day ♪</i>

32:35.953 --> 32:39.415
<i>♪ The more you let her go ♪</i>

32:39.499 --> 32:42.335
<i>♪ The less she walks away ♪</i>

32:42.418 --> 32:45.672
<i>♪ I'll never</i>
<i>waste your time ♪</i>

32:45.755 --> 32:48.716
<i>♪ Say it wasn't true ♪</i>

32:48.800 --> 32:50.176
<i>♪ It blows my m-m-mind ♪</i>

32:52.387 --> 32:53.846
<i>♪ The things</i>
<i>we're living through ♪</i>

32:53.930 --> 32:55.640
<i>♪ Help me wake up ♪</i>

32:55.723 --> 32:59.769
<i>♪ Break my fall ♪</i>

32:59.852 --> 33:03.106
<i>[quirky music]</i>

33:03.189 --> 33:07.235
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:07.318 --> 33:10.071
[owl hoots]

33:10.154 --> 33:13.241
- I'm guessing you didn't find
the keys to the cab.

33:13.324 --> 33:14.701
- No.

33:14.784 --> 33:17.412
But I found an old guitar.

33:17.495 --> 33:20.039
- [sighs]

33:20.123 --> 33:21.958
You promised if I let you
take me to dinner,

33:22.041 --> 33:23.084
we'd get to the prom
before 8:30.

33:23.167 --> 33:25.128
I knew it was a bad idea
to go out to dinner

33:25.211 --> 33:27.672
which is why I tried
to talk you out of--

33:27.755 --> 33:29.215
- Uh...

33:29.298 --> 33:30.216
- What?

33:30.299 --> 33:31.050
- Uh...

33:31.592 --> 33:34.303
- [screams]

33:34.387 --> 33:35.471
Oh, my God!

33:35.555 --> 33:39.517
[screaming]

33:39.600 --> 33:42.019
-<i> ♪ Gonna be a while tonight ♪</i>

33:43.980 --> 33:47.817
<i>♪ And I know you're with me ♪</i>

33:49.152 --> 33:53.865
<i>♪ But I need you</i>
<i>in my sight ♪</i>

33:53.948 --> 33:55.491
<i>♪ So say you can be ♪</i>

33:55.575 --> 33:57.368
- [blows]

33:58.536 --> 34:00.580
<i>♪ 'Cause missing you</i>
<i>is like... ♪</i>

34:00.663 --> 34:03.124
- What are you doing?

34:03.207 --> 34:04.959
- I was blowing in your ear.

34:05.042 --> 34:07.420
I read that boys like that.

34:07.503 --> 34:09.380
- You got my ear all wet.

34:09.464 --> 34:10.255
- One second.

34:12.550 --> 34:14.092
Let me swab it for you.

34:15.469 --> 34:18.139
- This may be
the weirdest moment of my life.

34:21.559 --> 34:23.936
- So when I was in fourth
grade, I figured out

34:24.020 --> 34:26.606
I can make noises that sound
like animals underwater.

34:26.688 --> 34:27.315
Listen.

34:27.398 --> 34:32.320
[making animal noises]

34:32.402 --> 34:39.577
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:39.659 --> 34:40.995
- I mean, when Mr. Takato
first had me stirring

34:41.078 --> 34:42.996
the tuna fish,
I thought,

34:43.080 --> 34:44.498
"Okay, this guy
is off his nut."

34:44.581 --> 34:46.708
And then when he had me
stomping the grapes--

34:46.793 --> 34:49.670
- There is no Mr. Takato!
- What?

34:49.754 --> 34:51.922
Why would I make up--
- Hey.

34:52.005 --> 34:54.342
I hear you got a new car?
- Oh, God.

34:54.425 --> 34:55.802
- That's right.

34:55.885 --> 34:57.887
It's a stick shift,
which I now know how to drive.

34:57.970 --> 34:59.806
- I'm gonna go get some punch.

34:59.889 --> 35:02.016
- Bring me back some.

35:03.935 --> 35:05.937
So where's Brooke?

35:06.020 --> 35:08.356
- She dumped me.
She said I'm not exciting.

35:08.439 --> 35:11.943
Can you believe that?
- No, I can't.

35:12.026 --> 35:14.153
- So come show me
your new car.

35:14.237 --> 35:14.278
- Okay.

35:17.406 --> 35:25.164
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:27.375 --> 35:28.960
- And now there's mud on it!
Ugh!

35:29.043 --> 35:32.129
[groaning, grunting]

35:36.134 --> 35:38.719
Ooh.
[screams]

35:38.803 --> 35:43.057
Well, this is exactly how
I wanted to spend my prom.

35:43.850 --> 35:46.727
- Think of this as an adventure

35:46.811 --> 35:49.397
that no one wants to be on.

35:49.480 --> 35:50.731
- Get him!

35:50.815 --> 35:51.524
[all yelling]

35:51.607 --> 35:55.027
- [screams]

35:59.240 --> 36:02.118
- What was that about?
- Are you okay?

36:02.201 --> 36:03.452
- Yeah, I'm fine.

36:03.536 --> 36:05.288
Get up.

36:07.790 --> 36:09.292
- Sorry.

36:09.375 --> 36:10.167
- Get up.

36:12.920 --> 36:15.381
- We thought
you were the evil ones.

36:15.464 --> 36:16.549
- Evil ones?

36:16.632 --> 36:17.633
- What are you guys
nerding on about?

36:17.717 --> 36:20.928
- Black Doomsday?
- The end of the world.

36:21.012 --> 36:21.846
- Are we the only survivors?

36:21.929 --> 36:23.806
- The world hasn't ended.

36:23.890 --> 36:25.057
- We just had lasagna.

36:25.141 --> 36:27.226
- The world is not doo-med?

36:27.310 --> 36:29.145
- Do you wanna know
what's doo-med?

36:29.228 --> 36:31.272
Prom night is doo-med.
- Lola.

36:31.355 --> 36:32.440
- It is!

36:32.523 --> 36:33.941
My dress is ruined,
the dance is half over,

36:34.025 --> 36:36.110
and Zoey is
not even going--

36:36.193 --> 36:37.778
- How come Zoey
is not going?

36:37.862 --> 36:39.322
- She and James broke up.

36:39.405 --> 36:41.157
- Zoey has no date?
- You can't ask her.

36:41.240 --> 36:43.451
I'm way better friends
with Zoey.

36:43.534 --> 36:45.745
- But what if the world
does end?

36:45.828 --> 36:47.121
- If it's gonna end,

36:47.204 --> 36:48.831
let it end after
I've danced with Zoey.

36:48.915 --> 36:50.666
- Not if I get there first!

36:50.750 --> 36:51.876
- [yelling indistinctly]

36:51.959 --> 36:54.837
[all yelling indistinctly]

36:54.921 --> 36:58.507
[screaming]

36:58.591 --> 36:59.508
- Now what?

36:59.592 --> 37:00.635
- Follow the nerds.

37:03.512 --> 37:06.474
<i>[somber music]</i>

37:06.557 --> 37:14.315
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:14.941 --> 37:17.401
[phone rings]

37:21.906 --> 37:23.449
- Hello?

37:23.532 --> 37:24.825
<i>CHASE: Hey, Zo.</i>

37:24.909 --> 37:26.243
- Chase.
How's England?

37:26.327 --> 37:29.497
<i>CHASE: Oh, you know,</i>
<i>boiled food,</i>

37:29.580 --> 37:31.958
<i>people driving on the wrong</i>
<i>side of the street.</i>

37:32.041 --> 37:33.793
<i>You've seen movies.</i>

37:33.876 --> 37:35.127
- I have.

37:36.087 --> 37:38.547
<i>CHASE: How are you doin'?</i>

37:38.631 --> 37:40.967
- Um, okay, sorta.

37:41.050 --> 37:42.385
<i>CHASE: Sorta?</i>

37:42.468 --> 37:44.762
<i>That doesn't sound</i>
<i>very Zoeyish.</i>

37:44.845 --> 37:47.348
- Yeah, well, I haven't had
the best week.

37:47.431 --> 37:50.226
<i>CHASE: Oh.</i>
<i>Well, what's wrong?</i>

37:50.810 --> 37:53.479
- I don't know.

37:53.562 --> 37:54.814
<i>CHASE: Wait.</i>

37:54.897 --> 37:57.233
<i>I thought PCA was having</i>
<i>their prom tonight?</i>

37:57.316 --> 38:00.027
- We are.
I blew it off.

38:00.111 --> 38:02.029
<i>CHASE: How come?</i>

38:02.113 --> 38:04.699
- Because I didn't wanna go
by myself.

38:04.782 --> 38:06.117
<i>CHASE: Ohhh.</i>

38:06.200 --> 38:07.743
<i>Then turn around.</i>

38:07.827 --> 38:10.830
<i>[sweeping music]</i>

38:10.913 --> 38:15.876
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:15.960 --> 38:17.586
- Chase.

38:21.674 --> 38:22.717
Chase!

38:25.469 --> 38:25.845
- Ahh!

38:25.928 --> 38:28.639
[thud]

38:28.723 --> 38:30.683
<i>[quirky music]</i>

38:30.766 --> 38:34.562
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:34.645 --> 38:37.148
I'm all right.
I'm okay.

38:37.231 --> 38:38.858
I just lost my balance!

38:38.941 --> 38:41.652
Concrete!
Ow! Ow!

38:41.736 --> 38:42.445
- Chase!

38:45.698 --> 38:48.451
Are you okay?

38:48.534 --> 38:50.202
- I think so.

38:50.286 --> 38:51.662
- Your arm's bleeding.

38:53.956 --> 38:55.458
- It's okay.

38:55.541 --> 38:58.377
I think I lost all feeling
in this arm anyway.

38:59.045 --> 39:01.756
- Can you feel this?

39:01.839 --> 39:03.632
- Kind of.

39:03.716 --> 39:05.634
<i>[gentle music]</i>

39:05.718 --> 39:11.932
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:12.016 --> 39:12.391
- How about this?

39:14.143 --> 39:21.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:33.079 --> 39:36.082
- Yeah, I felt that.

39:37.041 --> 39:38.292
- Good.

39:44.048 --> 39:46.050
- Nice wheels.
- Yep.

39:46.133 --> 39:48.511
Wanna take it for a spin?

39:48.594 --> 39:51.097
- Oh, I don't know
how to drive a stick shift.

39:52.723 --> 39:53.516
- Wanna learn?

39:56.227 --> 39:59.355
WOMAN: ♪ Back to the zero ♪

40:02.024 --> 40:03.400
♪ Back to square one ♪

40:06.862 --> 40:11.826
♪ Back to the train wreck
of the ones... ♪

40:11.909 --> 40:13.953
- You smell so good,

40:14.036 --> 40:16.622
like cinnamon sticks.

40:16.705 --> 40:18.666
- Uh, thanks?

40:18.749 --> 40:21.919
- Let's see if your lips
taste like cinnamon sticks.

40:22.002 --> 40:24.046
- Ahh!

40:24.130 --> 40:27.299
[sputtering]

40:27.383 --> 40:28.134
- What's wrong?

40:28.217 --> 40:30.469
- I don't wanna kiss you!

40:30.553 --> 40:32.138
- Why wouldn't you
wanna kiss me?

40:32.221 --> 40:33.305
My lips are moist.

40:33.389 --> 40:34.265
- Because I love Quinn!

40:34.348 --> 40:36.559
[music stops, crowd gasps]

40:39.103 --> 40:40.896
- Wh-what?

40:40.980 --> 40:41.438
- You love Quinn?

40:44.191 --> 40:46.318
- That's right!

40:55.119 --> 40:58.164
I love Quinn Pensky!

41:00.291 --> 41:03.752
- And I love Logan Reese!

41:03.836 --> 41:05.713
[crowd awws]

41:07.673 --> 41:09.466
- You used me?

41:13.053 --> 41:16.015
<i>[music swells]</i>

41:16.098 --> 41:20.895
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:20.978 --> 41:21.896
- Hey!

41:21.979 --> 41:30.738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:32.907 --> 41:34.700
- [sobbing]

41:40.873 --> 41:42.166
- Stir the tuna.

41:42.249 --> 41:43.167
- Why do you keep saying that?

41:43.250 --> 41:45.044
- Stomp the grapes.

41:45.127 --> 41:47.755
- And that?

41:47.838 --> 41:49.131
- [sobbing]

41:49.215 --> 41:51.800
[tires squeal]

41:51.884 --> 41:52.718
[both screaming]

42:00.184 --> 42:02.519
- You hit Stacey.

42:04.021 --> 42:06.815
- [groans]

42:09.860 --> 42:11.278
- Stacey!

42:11.362 --> 42:12.571
- He made me drive
a stick shift.

42:12.655 --> 42:14.782
- Oh, he grape'd
when he should have tuna'd.

42:17.409 --> 42:20.162
Stacey, say somethin'.

42:20.246 --> 42:23.165
- What struck me?

42:23.249 --> 42:24.750
Something slammed
into my side.

42:24.833 --> 42:27.294
Ooh, I'm gonna be
seriously sore.

42:27.378 --> 42:30.381
- Did you hear her?
- Yeah.

42:30.464 --> 42:33.133
- Stacey's "S"s sound normal.

42:33.217 --> 42:35.469
- Say something else.

42:35.552 --> 42:37.388
- My name is Stacey Dillsen,

42:37.471 --> 42:39.640
and I'm from Swampscott,
Massachusetts.

42:39.723 --> 42:40.140
[gasps]

42:40.224 --> 42:42.226
Oh, my God!

42:42.309 --> 42:44.311
My "S"s sound perfect!

42:45.813 --> 42:48.190
My sister Susanne
is a staff sergeant

42:48.274 --> 42:50.442
at St. Steven's hospital
in Mississippi.

42:50.526 --> 42:52.361
[cheers and applause]

42:52.444 --> 42:53.737
- Oh, yeah!

42:57.408 --> 42:58.534
- I can't believe it.

42:58.617 --> 43:02.329
- I know!
She talks perfectly now.

43:03.455 --> 43:05.666
Chase, she talks
perfectly now.

43:09.253 --> 43:10.838
Chase!
- Michael!

43:10.921 --> 43:13.048
[laughter]
- Chase.

43:13.132 --> 43:16.343
- All right, all right.
Don't break my boyfriend.

43:16.427 --> 43:17.553
- Your-your-your-
your boyfriend?

43:17.636 --> 43:19.430
- Yeah, we just got done--
- Chase!

43:19.513 --> 43:22.308
What-what--
Chase!

43:22.391 --> 43:24.310
Chase! Chase!

43:24.393 --> 43:25.853
- All right,
can we all go dance now

43:25.936 --> 43:27.062
before the prom is over?

43:27.146 --> 43:28.022
- Yeah, let's dance!

43:28.105 --> 43:30.024
- Let's dance.
I--but wait.

43:30.107 --> 43:32.484
I gotta move my car first.
I'll meet you there in sec.

43:35.404 --> 43:35.654
Chase!

43:42.286 --> 43:44.330
[horn honks]

43:44.413 --> 43:45.205
- Let's dance.

43:45.289 --> 43:48.208
<i>MAN: ♪ Where I do go ♪</i>

43:48.292 --> 43:50.878
<i>♪ Now that I know ♪</i>

43:50.961 --> 43:52.379
<i>♪ This is who ♪</i>

43:52.463 --> 43:55.924
<i>♪ I'm always going to be ♪</i>

43:56.008 --> 43:57.468
[music stops]

44:10.439 --> 44:12.566
Mr. Takato?

44:14.485 --> 44:16.737
- Hello, Michael.

44:16.820 --> 44:18.655
- Would you please
come tell my girlfriend

44:18.739 --> 44:19.782
that you really work
here at PCA

44:19.865 --> 44:22.368
and that you thought me
to drive a stick shift?

44:22.451 --> 44:23.786
- Oh, I can't do that.

44:25.871 --> 44:26.663
- Why not?

44:26.747 --> 44:28.749
- Because I do not exist.

44:32.544 --> 44:34.546
[clicks tongue]

44:34.630 --> 44:37.841
<i>[mystical music]</i>

44:37.925 --> 44:45.682
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:49.520 --> 44:50.104
- ♪ You and me ♪

44:50.187 --> 44:51.605
♪ Hanging out ♪

44:51.688 --> 44:54.274
♪ Talking about everything ♪

44:54.358 --> 44:56.443
♪ You and me ♪

44:56.527 --> 44:57.444
♪ Just hanging out ♪

44:57.528 --> 45:00.406
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

45:00.489 --> 45:01.949
- Here we go!

45:02.032 --> 45:04.368
- ♪ Here we go ♪

45:04.451 --> 45:07.246
♪ Everybody come together ♪

45:07.329 --> 45:10.332
- Come on.
- ♪ Here we go ♪

45:10.416 --> 45:13.335
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

45:13.419 --> 45:15.170
- Michael.
- ♪ You and me ♪

45:15.254 --> 45:16.630
♪ Figured out ♪

45:16.713 --> 45:19.633
♪ What this life's all about ♪

45:19.716 --> 45:22.636
♪ Could we make it fun ♪

45:22.719 --> 45:25.806
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

45:25.889 --> 45:27.850
- Got any plans
for the summer?

45:27.933 --> 45:28.976
- Nope. Why?

45:29.059 --> 45:30.060
- Do you wanna spend it
with me in Hawaii?

45:30.144 --> 45:32.521
- Hawaii?

45:32.604 --> 45:34.690
You and me all summer?
- Mm-hmm.

45:34.773 --> 45:38.152
- Yes!
- ♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

45:38.235 --> 45:38.986
♪ You and me, you and me ♪

45:39.069 --> 45:40.821
♪ Hanging out, hanging out ♪

45:40.904 --> 45:41.613
♪ Talking about,
talking about ♪

45:41.697 --> 45:44.116
♪ Everything, everything ♪

45:44.199 --> 45:45.576
♪ You and me, you and me ♪

45:45.659 --> 45:46.493
♪ Just hanging out,
hanging out ♪

45:46.577 --> 45:49.246
- Oh, Zoey is with Chase.

45:49.329 --> 45:51.081
- Ohh.

45:52.374 --> 45:53.876
- Hey, there's a girl.

45:53.959 --> 45:55.669
- And her foot's stuck
in the fence.

45:55.752 --> 45:57.171
- [yelling indistinctly]

45:57.254 --> 45:58.630
[all yelling]

45:58.714 --> 46:01.425
- ♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

46:01.508 --> 46:05.137
[cheers and applause]

46:05.220 --> 46:06.680
- I'm here!

46:06.763 --> 46:09.349
- It's my fault we're late.

46:09.433 --> 46:10.684
- Did we miss anything good?

46:10.768 --> 46:12.519
- Nah, you didn't miss much.

46:12.603 --> 46:13.937
- Nothing important.

46:14.021 --> 46:17.441
- Oh, good, 'cause--
Chase!

46:17.524 --> 46:19.526
- Give me the love.

46:19.610 --> 46:21.236
- I'm gonna give you
some love.

46:21.320 --> 46:22.821
[cheering]
- Yes.

46:22.905 --> 46:24.281
- Yes!

46:24.364 --> 46:27.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:27.534 --> 46:27.951
- Well, let's dance!

46:31.288 --> 46:33.499
- ♪ I told you 20 times ♪

46:34.750 --> 46:35.918
♪ I need to be with you ♪

46:38.420 --> 46:40.464
♪ You're always on my mind ♪

46:40.547 --> 46:41.965
- Yeah, baby.

46:42.049 --> 46:43.967
MAN: ♪ You gotta feel it too ♪

46:45.636 --> 46:47.012
{\an8}♪ I wanna treat you right ♪

46:48.514 --> 46:51.517
{\an8}♪ And be a family ♪

46:53.352 --> 46:55.103
{\an8}♪ Well every day and night ♪

46:56.647 --> 46:59.066
{\an8}♪ That's where I wanna be ♪

46:59.942 --> 47:02.277
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: ♪ If you wanna play ♪</i>

47:02.361 --> 47:04.530
{\an8}<i>♪ Come and play today ♪</i>

47:04.613 --> 47:07.950
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's just get away, yeah ♪</i>

47:09.326 --> 47:11.078
{\an8}<i>♪ I will make you see ♪</i>

47:11.161 --> 47:12.412
{\an8}<i>♪ All of the things ♪</i>

